[SN]TITLE[SN]
Reading stages VJ ceremony to mark 70th anniversary

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Wreaths have been laid at a service in Reading to mark the 70th anniversary of VJ Day.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A memorial event was held at the town's Burma Star Memorial in Forbury Gardens to mark the surrender of Japan and the end of World War Two.
Wreaths were laid during the ceremony, led by the Mayor of Reading councillor Sarah Hacker.
Cllr Hacker said: "It's a time for reflection and it is our duty to honour the fallen. We must never forget them."
